@node "f1-preview" " Preview "

F1 Preivew
==========

Jacques Villenuve starts this years FIA Formula One World
Championship as favorite and that's is hardly surprising
considering his performances in his debut season. Now,
Villenuve has a years expierience behind him - he knows the
car, he knows the team and he knows the circuits.
              You can be sure that Villenuve will come under
a lot of pressure from his new team mate Heinz-Harald
Frentzen. Frentzen has been in Formula One ever since 1994
so he carries more expierince than Villenuve. He has however
got the tasks of fitting in with team and learning the car
to contend with. Know one really knows how quick Frentzen is
but it wont be too long before we find out.
              Hot on the heels of the Williams pairing will
be double world champion Michael Schumacher. The big
question is "Have Ferrari produced a car reliable and quick
enough for Schumacher to take the title in?" Last season
Ferrari struggled quite a bit with reliability which cost
them precious points. Schumacher's team mate will once again
be Eddie Irvine from Northern Ireland. Last year Irvine was
given little testing although so far this year it has been
a lot closer. It will be interesting to see how quick he is
in relation to Schumacher.
              Reigning world champion Damon Hill moves to the
TWR Arrows team from Williams. The team will be run by Tom
Walkinshaw who has lots of sucsess in other motor sport
catogaries including victory at Le Mans and sucsess in the
World Sports Car Championship. Walkinshaw was also involved
in Michael Schumacher's 1994 title sucsess. So far, testing
hasn't been going too well for the team which will be making
use of Bridgestone tyres. Joining Hill in the team will be
Brazilian Pedro Diniz who makes move from Ligier.
              Last year's Monaco winner, Olivier Panis, has
been setting some sensational times while testing for Alain
Prost's new team - Prost (formerally known as Ligier). Most
people believe these times to be down to the Bridgestone
tyres that the team is using and Panis hopes to use the
advantage gained to get Prost up into the 'big four'. With
Bridgestone's presence next year it will be interesting to
see how Goodyear cope with the threat.
              Ralf Schumacher - brother of Michael - will be
one of the drivers for the Jordan Peugeot team this season.
He comes to Formula One after taking the Formula Nippon
(Japanese F3000) championship last year. This will be a year
in which Jordan must perform if they want to keep their 
works Peugeot engines for next season. Schumacher Jnr will 
be joined the Jordan team by highly rated Italian Giancarlo
Fisichella.
              1997 sees Lola entering Formula One with the
backing of Mastercard. Their drivers will be Italian
Vincenzo Sospiri and Brazilian Ricardo Rosset who finished
1st and 2nd (respectivley) in the 1995 FIA F3000
championship. Lola have been involved in Formula One before
but as a chassis suplier rather than a team. For their first
year they will use customer Ford V8 engines so don't expect
too much.
              Also entering Formula One in 1997 will be the
Stewart team. Run by former champion Jackie and his son
Paul, the team will make use of works Ford V10 engines for
at least the next five years. The driving team consists off
Rubens Barrichello and the up and coming Dane Jan Magnussen.
Both have been setting encouraging testing times.

@endnode

