@node "cart-preview" " Preview"

CART Season Preview
===================

Indycar may have changed its name to CART but this season's
favorite has the advantage of continuity as he and reigning champion
Jimmy Vasser stick with Ganassi.
              Zanardi shown strong form in his first year and could
have perhaps even taken the championship had it not been for a string
of mechanical failures early on. During the second half of the season
Zanardi scored more points than any other driver and has generally
been found near the top of the time sheets in pre season testing.
              As for his team mate Jimmy Vasser, he will have a fight
on his hands if he wants to hang onto this years title. He sarted the
season well last year with a string of wins but his performances faded
as the season went on. Vasser too has been near the top of the testing
times so he'll more than likley be following Zanardi closley. Last
year, both he and Zanardi got on well but two evenley matched drivers
in a top team could well spell disaster...
              Mauricio Gulgemin and team mate Mark Blundell may
spring a surprise or two going on the times both have been setting in
testing. Penske also should never be discounted with the strong 
driving line up of Al Unser Jnr and Paul Tracey. Newman/Hass meanwhile
will switch to Swift chassis this season (the first year in the
championship for Swift) and with Michael Andretti and Christian
Fittapaldi should not be discounted. Also keep an eye out for Richie
Hern who has switched from CART's rival the IRL and has been setting
some reasnably good testing times. Team Rahal duo, Bobby Rahal and
Bryan Herta should also come on strong.
                British interest will be increased his year as Dario
Franchitti has signed to drive for Team Hogan. The previous two years
Franchitti has driven in the ITC (International Touring Car
Championship) and shown he fully deserves this oppertunity. This first
year will be difficult for him as he learns the ropes but expect rapid
progress through out the season.
                 Live European coverage of this years championship
will again be provided by Satilite TV station, Eurosport of what
should tunrn out to be an extremly excieting single seater
championship.

